    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. GENE GREEN of Texas:H.J. Res. 65.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article V of the United States Constitution, which grantsCongress the authority, whenever two-thirds of both chambersdeem it necessary, to propose amendments to the Constitution.[Page H1086]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
